snippet: A standoff between supporters of the ousted president, Mohamed Morsi, and soldiers at a mosque ended with no reports of casualties, but it was emblematic of Egypt’s wider chaos.
abstract: Egyptian soldiers storm mosque in Cairo where supporters of ousted Pres Mohamed Morsi had taken shelter, briefly turning central thoroughfare into a war zone; attack is further sign that Egypt's new military rulers are struggling to impose order days after security forces killed hundreds of antigovernment Islamists.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and MAYY EL SHEIKH

lead_paragraph: A standoff between supporters of the ousted president, Mohamed Morsi, and soldiers at a mosque ended with no reports of casualties, but it was emblematic of Egypt’s wider chaos.

headline.main: Soldiers Storm a Mosque in Cairo, as Egyptian Leaders Struggle for Order
